    public class KeyedCheckpointedTSet<K,V>
extends KeyedPersistedTSet<K,V>
    This is a shadow KeyedPersistedTSet to add the checkpointing capability. It does not have the sink that would store the data, because the purpose of this tset is to expose the data that was stored by a KeyedPersistedTSet.

    When this tset is executed, it would wrap DiskPartitionBackedSource from DiskPartitionBackedSourceWrapper and return a CheckpointedSourceOp as the INode for the underlying task.
